The paper focuses on the security of a proximity-based system, which suggests that it falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The system also involves wireless communication and distance measurement, indicating that it could be related to networked systems (cs.NI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses possible countermeasures and limitations, which suggests that it could be related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) for developing and evaluating such countermeasures.
